Step 1: Calculate Debt to Equity Ratio  
• From the balance sheet, Total Current Liabilities = 1,548,001.20  
• Total Owner's Equity = 14,105,265.77  
• Debt to Equity Ratio = Total Liabilities / Total Owner's Equity  
  = 1,548,001.20 / 14,105,265.77  
  ≈ 0.11  

Step 2: Calculate Net Profit Margin  
• From the income statement, Net Profit = 1,105,265.77  
• Total Revenue = 5,760,023.09  
• Net Profit Margin = (Net Profit / Total Revenue) × 100%  
  = (1,105,265.77 / 5,760,023.09) × 100%  
  ≈ 19.19%  

Step 3: Calculate Operating Cash Flow to Current Liabilities Ratio  
• From the cash flow statement, Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities = 803,237.11  
• Total Current Liabilities = 1,548,001.20  
• Operating Cash Flow to Current Liabilities Ratio = 803,237.11 / 1,548,001.20  
  ≈ 0.52  

Thus, the final answer is:

{
  "solution": {
    "Debt to Equity Ratio": "0.11",
    "Net Profit Margin": "19.19%",
    "operating cash flow to current liabilities ratio": "0.52"
  }
}
